      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation — CFD vs. reference simulation",
      "description": "The CFD model was assessed by comparing predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values against those generated by a high-fidelity reference numerical simulation of the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Across all five flow-speed operating points, RH values predicted by the subject model agreed with the reference simulation to within 4.2%, well below the RH < 1.0 acceptance threshold. The reference simulation incorporates a validated power-law hemolysis model calibrated against published literature data, and is therefore considered a reliable surrogate for direct experimental comparison. This approach is regarded as functionally equivalent to experimental validation given the maturity of the reference model.",
